messages.message: Email addresses in the top session go outside the element, we should use ellipsis here if it expands outside the available space
Good feedback - this will typically render with first/last name, but we should have ellipses in either case
We also should do this with the name of the user

Also related, we donâ€™t handle spaces in the username correctly.
https://www.loom.com/share/a72f1b4ef09e466bb4e87d783567b07d?sid=01a6435f-d58b-44c8-a901-d2d993b46d57

We recently migrated all usernames and emails to use lowercase. There are a bunch UIs relying on the assumption that the personal workspace name = username. See https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C04TSMWLPAS/p1700100432259529.

Basically, if the personal workspace name = username, this won't happen and the user will see the attached screens
